{"name":"Heretical Priest","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>Insightful, roll 3d6+2 for Presence. Frail, roll 3d6-2 for Strength. Roll a d8 on the weapons table and may use Powers while wearing medium armor. You begin with one of the following:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 Sacred shepherd&rsquo;s crook</li>\n<li>2 Stolen Mitre</li>\n<li>3 List of Sins</li>\n<li>4 The Blasphemous Nechrubel Bible</li>\n<li>5 Stones taken from Thel-Emas' Lost Temple</li>\n<li>666 (Wrong Jesus) Crucifix</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Unholy Origins</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1. Galgenbeck, near the cathedral of the Two-Headed Basilisks.</li>\n<li>2. Massacred Alli&aacute;ns cult, sole survivor.</li>\n<li>3. The crypts of Grift.</li>\n<li>4. Temple ruins in the Valley if the Unfortunate Undead.</li>\n<li>5. One of the many Graven-Tosk thief-tunnels.</li>\n<li>6 Secret Bergen Chrypt church.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","description":"Hunted by the Two-Headed Basilisks of the One True Faith, this heretic can be found raving in ruins, traipsing endlessly down dusty roads and desecrating cathedrals by night.","omenDie":"1d4","startingHitPoints":"1d8","startingSilver":"3d6*10"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classes/hereticalpriest.png","effects":[],"_id":"6kqXaGsRwi7zUrVk"}
{"name":"Esoteric Hermit","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>Wise, roll 3D6+2 for Presence. Weak, roll 3D6&minus;2 for Strength. Ordinary starting equipment plus one random scroll (sacred or unclean). Roll a D4 on the weapons table and D2 on the armor table. You also begin with one of the following:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>01 Master of Fate</li>\n<li>02 Book of Boiling Blood</li>\n<li>03 Speaker of Truths</li>\n<li>04 Initiate of the Invisible College</li>\n<li>05 Bard of the Undying</li>\n<li>06 Hawk as Weapon</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Eldritch Origins, d6</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 Awakening, adult, in a ritual circle underneath the northern bridge to Grift.</li>\n<li>2 Wandered, memoryless, from the mouth of a cavern at the cliffs of Terion.</li>\n<li>3 Single child survivor of an incident in the Valley of the Unfortunate Undead.</li>\n<li>4 Dying of plague in a Bergen Chrypt hovel, you touched something from outside.</li>\n<li>5 An average individual until you encountered something in a dim glade in Sarkash.</li>\n<li>6 Raised on a lonely island in Lake Onda. No one else has ever heard of this island and you can&rsquo;t return.</li>\n</ul>","description":"The stone of your cave is one with the stars. Silence and perfection. Now the chaos of a fallen world disturbs your rituals and the caul of night grows blacker than your cavern’s gloom. Irritating!","omenDie":"1d4","startingHitPoints":"1d4","startingSilver":"1d6*10"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classes/esoterichermit.png","effects":[],"_id":"CE5G9pwFpD66JGIy"}
{"name":"Fanged Deserter","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>Built like a Bull, roll 3d6+2 for Strength. Not a Bright Spark, roll 3d6-1 for Agility and Presence. Normal Agility tests are DR14 instead of DR12, excluding defense. Illiterate; you are incapable of understanding scrolls. If you begin with one then reroll, eat it or use it as toilet paper. You also begin with one of the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 Crumpled Monster Mask</li>\n<li>2 The Brown Scimitar of Galgenbeck</li>\n<li>3 Wizard Teeth</li>\n<li>4 Old Sig&ucirc;rd&rsquo;s sling</li>\n<li>5 Ancient Gore-Hound</li>\n<li>6 The Shoe of Death's Horse</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>EARLIEST MEMORIES, D6</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 A burnt-black building in Sarkash. Your home?</li>\n<li>2 A derelict rotting ship rolling endlessly across a grey sea.</li>\n<li>3 A brothel in Schleswig. Quite a friendly environment.</li>\n<li>4 Sleeping with dogs in the corner of an inn, waiting for someone to return.</li>\n<li>5 Following an army in eastern W&auml;stland.</li>\n<li>6 Suckling a wolf in the wild of Bergen Chrypt.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","description":"You have thirty or so friends who never let you down: YOUR TEETH. Disloyal, deranged or simply uncontrollable, any group that didn’t boot you out you left anyway. But your parliament of teeth—enormous, protruding, thick and sharp—have always been your allies. Bite attack: DR10 to attack, d6 damage. You must be close to your target. 1–2 on d6 chance the enemy gets a free attack.","omenDie":"1d2","startingHitPoints":"1d8","startingSilver":"2d6*10"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classes/fangeddeserter.png","effects":[],"_id":"XBawgwHUNmBP9nkR"}
{"name":"Gutterborn Scum","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>Small, roll 3d6&minus;2 for Strength. Stealthy, all Presence and Agility tests have their DR reduced by 2 (normal tests are DR10 instead of DR12). Roll d6 on the weapon table and d2 on the armor table. You also begin with one specialty:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 Coward's Jab</li>\n<li>2 Filthy Fingersmith</li>\n<li>3 Abominable Gob Lobber</li>\n<li>4 Escaping Fate</li>\n<li>5 Excreta Stealth</li>\n<li>6 Dodging Death</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The first time the Scum gets better another specialty is rolled. From the second time the Scum gets better it&rsquo;s possible to reroll these two specialities or just one.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","description":"An ill star smiled upon your birth. Poverty, crime and bad parenting didn’t help either. In your community an honest day’s work was never an option. Not that you ever tried, what are you, some kind of mug? A razor blade and a moonless night are worth a week of chump-work.","omenDie":"1d2","startingHitPoints":"1d6","startingSilver":"1d6*10"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classes/gutterbornscum.png","effects":[],"_id":"ZUG0dYItT6EjuR8r"}
{"name":"Occult Herbmaster","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>Tough as wood, roll 3d6+2 Toughness. Low in protein, roll 3d6-2 Strength. Roll d6 on the weapons table and d2 on the armor table. You carry a portable laboratory and continually search for frequently expended ingredients. Daily you have the materials to create two randomly determined decoctions and can brew a total of d4 doses. If unused they lose vitality after 24 hours.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 Red Poison</li>\n<li>2 Ezumiels Vapor</li>\n<li>3 Southern Frog Stew</li>\n<li>4 Elixir Vitalis</li>\n<li>5 Spider-Owl Soup</li>\n<li>6 Fernor's Philtre</li>\n<li>7 Hyphos Enervating Snuff</li>\n<li>8 Black Poison</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;(d8) Probably raised in&hellip; but may also come from</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1-3: calm isolation in the Sarkash dark.</li>\n<li>4: the illegal midnight markets of Schleswig.</li>\n<li>5: the heretic isle of Cr&euml;lut, two nautical miles east of Grift.</li>\n<li>6: the old frozen runs not far from Alli&aacute;ns.</li>\n<li>7: a little witches cottage in Galgenbeck.</li>\n<li>8: the runs of the Shadow King's manse, thick with memories of mushrooms and smoke.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","description":"","omenDie":"1d2","startingHitPoints":"1d8","startingSilver":"2d6*10"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classes/occultherbmaster.png","effects":[],"_id":"o6mKMV8NZYhru8hF"}
{"name":"Wretched Royalty","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>Painfully average, you adjust no abilities. Roll a d8 on the weapons table. Roll a d4 on the armor table but reroll if you receive heavy armor. You begin with two of the following:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 The Blade of you Ancestors</li>\n<li>2 &lsquo;Poltroon&rsquo; the Court Jester</li>\n<li>3 Barbarister the Incredible Horse</li>\n<li>4 Hamfund the Squire</li>\n<li>5 The Snake-Skin Gift</li>\n<li>6 Horn of the Schleswig Lords!</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Things were going so well, until&hellip; (d6)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 your W&auml;stland palace was reduced to rubble.</li>\n<li>2 your caravan kingdom of Tveland fell into penury.</li>\n<li>3 King Fathmu IX's brother Zigmund, your father, was murdered.</li>\n<li>4 the southern empire of S&uuml;dglans sank into the sea.</li>\n<li>5 Anthelia demanded a gift of royal blood</li>\n<li>6 two young princes were kidnapped west of Bergen Chrypt and disappeared into the black crevasse of the eastern slopes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","description":"Bowed down only by the memories of your own lost glory, you could never submit to anyone else. Not you, of noble blood! (Not that you expect any of these peons to understand the depths of your sorrow.)","omenDie":"1d2","startingHitPoints":"1d6","startingSilver":"4d6*10"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classes/wretchedroyalty.png","effects":[],"_id":"yLbxKT7NsXjEYN13"}
